omy menu-item-object-category menu-item-6710\"><a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/category/recipes/miscellaneous/vegetables/\">vegetables</a></li>\n\t<li id=\"menu-item-6704\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-taxonomy menu-item-object-category menu-item-6704\"><a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/category/recipes/miscellaneous/dessert/\">dessert</a></li>\n\t<li id=\"menu-item-6705\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-taxonomy menu-item-object-category menu-item-6705\"><a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/category/recipes/miscellaneous/how-to/\">how-to</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li id=\"menu-item-17798\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-custom menu-item-object-custom menu-item-has-children menu-item-17798\"><a href=\"http://budgetbytes.ziplist.com/recipes/box\">Recipe Box</a>\n<ul class=\"sub-menu\">\n\t<li id=\"menu-item-17799\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-custom menu-item-object-custom menu-item-17799\"><a href=\"http://budgetbytes.ziplist.com/mylist\">Shopping List</a></li>\n\t<li id=\"menu-item-17800\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-custom menu-item-object-custom menu-item-17800\"><a href=\"http://budgetbytes.ziplist.com/recipes/meal_planner\">Meal Planner</a></li>\n\t<li id=\"menu-item-17801\" class=\"menu-item menu-item-type-custom menu-item-object-custom menu-item-17801\"><a href=\"http://budgetbytes.ziplist.com/deals\">Grocery Deals</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"right search\"><form method=\"get\" class=\"searchform search-form\" action=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/\" role=\"search\" ><input type=\"text\" value=\"search budget bytes\" name=\"s\" class=\"s search-input\" onfocus=\"if (&#039;search budget bytes&#039; === this.value) {this.value = &#039;&#039;;}\" onblur=\"if (&#039;&#039; === this.value) {this.value = &#039;search budget bytes&#039;;}\" /><input type=\"submit\" class=\"searchsubmit search-submit\" value=\"Search\" /></form></li></ul></div></div><div id=\"inner\"><div class=\"wrap\"><div id=\"content-sidebar-wrap\"><div id=\"content\" class=\"hfeed\"><div class=\"breadcrumb\">You are here: <a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/\" title=\"View Home\">Home</a> / <a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/category/recipes/\" title=\"View all items in recipes\">recipes</a> / <a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/category/recipes/breakfast/\" title=\"View all items in breakfast\">breakfast</a> / indian spiced oats w/ coconut milk</div><div class=\"post-13535 post type-post status-publish format-standard category-breakfast category-global category-indian category-oats category-vegan category-vegetarian entry\"><div class=\"post-info\"><span class=\"date published time\" title=\"2010-01-31T09:33:00+00:00\">01.31.10</span> </div><h1 class=\"entry-title\">indian spiced oats w/ coconut milk</h1> \n<div class=\"recipe-cost\">$2.80 recipe / $0.70 serving</div><div class=\"entry-content\"><p>I&#8217;ve been off the steel-cut oats bandwagon for a while because I&#8217;ve been addicted to my little breakfast egg quesadillas (I&#8217;ll post that soon because they&#8217;re too good to keep to myself). But, this week I got a hankering for the almighty oats. I didn&#8217;t realize how I missed their chewy goodness until now! Anyway, this little Indian pilaf inspired oat mixture turned out FANTASTIC. The spices, sweet raisins, crunchy almonds and super creamy coconut milk balance each other perfectly. This breakfast will make you feel like the Maharaja while only costing you $0.70!</p>\n<h2>Indian Spiced Oats with Coconut Milk</h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/Indian-Oats.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-17898 pin-it\" alt=\"Indian Spiced Oats\" src=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/Indian-Oats.jpg\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\"></a></p>\n<div class=\"easyrecipe\" itemscope itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Recipe\">\n<link itemprop=\"image\" href=\"http://lh4.ggpht.com/_OaYG005JPDs/S2WUsM_G3XI/AAAAAAAAAxQ/I5PKk7Qo4Rg/s800/Indian%20Oats.jpg\"/>\n<div itemprop=\"name\" class=\"ERSName\">indian spiced oats w/ coconut milk</div>\n<div class=\"ERSClear\">&nbsp;</div>\n<div class=\"ERSTopRight\">\n<div class=\"ERSSavePrint\"> <span class=\"ERSSaveBtnSpan\"><script type='text/javascript' src='http://www.ziplist.com/javascripts/wk.js'></script><a class='ziplist-button add-recipe large ERSSaveBtn' href='http://www.ziplist.com/webkitchen/button/add_recipe?as_partner=budgetbytes&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.budgetbytes.com%2F2010%2F01%2Findian-spiced-oats-w-coconut-milk%2F' target='_blank'>Save</a></span> <span class=\"ERSPrintBtnSpan\"><a class=\"ERSPrintBtn\" href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/easyrecipe-print/13535-0/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Print</a></span> </div>\n</p></div>\n<div class=\"ERSTimes\">\n<div class=\"ERSTime\">\n<div class=\"ERSTimeHeading\">Prep time</div>\n<div class=\"ERSTimeItem\"> <time itemprop=\"prepTime\" datetime=\"PT5M\">5 mins</time> </div>\n</p></div>\n<div class=\"ERSTime ERSTimeRight\">\n<div class=\"ERSTimeHeading\">Cook time</div>\n<div class=\"ERSTimeItem\"> <time itemprop=\"cookTime\" datetime=\"PT30M\">30 mins</time> </div>\n</p></div>\n<div class=\"ERSTime ERSTimeRight\">\n<div class=\"ERSTimeHeading\">Total time</div>\n<div class=\"ERSTimeItem\"> <time itemprop=\"totalTime\" datetime=\"PT35M\">35 mins</time> </div>\n</p></div>\n<div class=\"ERSClearLeft\">&nbsp;</div>\n</p></div>\n<div class=\"divERSHeadItems\">\n<div>Total Cost: <span itemprop=\"recipeCategory\">$2.80</span></div>\n<div>Cost Per Serving: <span itemprop=\"recipeCuisine\">$0.70</span></div>\n<div>Serves: <span itemprop=\"recipeYield\">4</span></div>\n</p></div>\n<div class=\"ERSIngredients\">\n<div class=\"ERSIngredientsHeader ERSHeading\">Ingredients</div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"ingredient\" itemprop=\"ingredients\">1 cup steel cut oats $0.70</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\" itemprop=\"ingredients\">&frac12; tsp salt $0.05</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\" itemprop=\"ingredients\">1 tsp cinnamon $0.10</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\" itemprop=\"ingredients\">&frac12; tsp ground ginger $0.05</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\" itemprop=\"ingredients\">&frac14; tsp ground cloves $0.05</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\" itemprop=\"ingredients\">&frac12; tsp vanilla extract $0.15</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\" itemprop=\"ingredients\">&frac14; cup brown sugar $0.12</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\" itemprop=\"ingredients\">&frac12; cup raisins $0.31</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\" itemprop=\"ingredients\">&frac14; cup sliced almonds $0.56</li>\n<li class=\"ingredient\" itemprop=\"ingredients\">1 cup light coconut milk $0.71</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"ERSClear\"></div>\n</p></div>\n<div class=\"ERSInstructions\">\n<div class=\"ERSInstructionsHeader ERSHeading\">Instructions</div>\n<ol>\n<li class=\"instruction\" itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">In a medium pot bring 4 cups of water and &frac12; tsp of salt to a boil. Once it reaches a rolling boil, add 1 cup of steel-cut oats. Reduce the heat to medium/low and let simmer for about 30 minutes or until the mixture is to your desired thickness.</li>\n<li class=\"instruction\" itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">As the mixture simmers, add the cinnamon, ginger, cloves, vanilla extract and brown sugar.</li>\n<li class=\"instruction\" itemprop=\"recipeInstructions\">Once the oats are finished cooking, divide it up into four servings and top each with 2 Tbsp of raisins, 1 Tbsp of sliced almonds and &frac14; cup of coconut milk. Dig in!</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"ERSClear\"></div>\n</p></div>\n<div class=\"endeasyrecipe\" title=\"style002a\" style=\"display: none\">3.2.2089</div>\n</p></div>\n<p><a name=\"more\"></a></p>\n<p><b>NOTE:</b> As with all of my oats, I divide them into resealable containers and keep them in the refrigerator. Then, in the morning, all I have to do is grab one and microwave it for a minute or so and I have a super hearty breakfast ready to go!</p>\n<p>Originally I intended to put cardamom in the spice mix but later realized that I didn&#8217;t have any. You can try this out with just about any combination of Indian spices and I&#8217;m sure it would be fantastic. I even thought about putting a chai tea bag in the water as it came to a boil before adding the oats. I&#8217;m not sure what kind of flavor that would add but it sounds like it could work!</p>\n<p><img alt=\"Indian Spiced Oats\" src=\"http://lh6.ggpht.com/_OaYG005JPDs/S2WUkzC1OeI/AAAAAAAAAxE/24iHBQN4bgQ/s400/Indian%20Oats%20w%20spoon.jpg\" class=\" pin-it\"></p>\n\n<div class=\"nr_related_placeholder\" data-permalink=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/2010/01/indian-spiced-oats-w-coconut-milk/\" data-title=\"indian spiced oats w/ coconut milk\"></div><div style=\"min-height:33px;\" class=\"really_simple_share really_simple_share_button robots-nocontent snap_nopreview\"><div class=\"really_simple_share_facebook_like\" style=\"width:90px;\"><iframe src=\"//www.facebook.com/plugins/like.php?href=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.budgetbytes.com%2F2010%2F01%2Findian-spiced-oats-w-coconut-milk%2F&amp;send=false&amp;layout=button_count&amp;width=90&amp;show_faces=false&amp;action=like&amp;colorscheme=light&amp;height=27&amp;locale=en_US\" \r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tscrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"border:none; overflow:hidden; width:90px; height:27px;\" allowTransparency=\"true\"></iframe></div><div class=\"really_simple_share_twitter\" style=\"width:90px;\"><a href=\"https://twitter.com/share\" class=\"twitter-share-button\" data-count=\"horizontal\"  data-text=\"indian spiced oats w/ coconut milk\" data-url=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/2010/01/indian-spiced-oats-w-coconut-milk/\"  data-via=\"\"   ></a></div><div class=\"really_simple_share_google1\" style=\"width:80px;\"><div class=\"g-plusone\" data-size=\"medium\" data-href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/2010/01/indian-spiced-oats-w-coconut-milk/\" ></div></div><div class=\"really_simple_share_pinterest\" style=\"width:90px;\"><a data-pin-config=\"beside\" href=\"https://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/\" data-p